{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Retain Disabled Students\u2019 Allowance (DSA) assistive technology funding",
        "additional_details": "We are calling on the Department for Education and Student Finance England to protect Disabled Students\u2019 Allowance (DSA) assistive technology funding and reject plans to restrict support to \u201cexceptional circumstances\u201d only.\r\n\r\nThese changes assume free or general tools can replace specialist support, despite limited evidence of equal outcomes. This risks widening inequality, increasing withdrawals, and reducing outcomes for disabled students. Reforms must be evidence-based, not cost-driven.",
        "background": "We\u2019re calling on the Government to protect Disabled Students\u2019 Allowance (DSA) assistive technology funding and reject plans to restrict support to \u201cexceptional circumstances\u201d only. These changes risk widening inequality and must be evidence-based, not cost-driven.",
